Isolate the Rightmost Set Bit. Write a function to isolate the rightmost set bit of an integer.

WTD: Given an integer, isolate the rightmost bit set to 1 in its binary representation. Use bitwise operations to find this bit while setting all other bits to 0.

(e.g.: I/P:  0b10100000; O/P: 0b00100000)



#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdint.h>

uint32_t fu(uint8_t da)
{
    for(int i =0; i<8 ; i++){
        if( da & (1<<i))
        {
            return (1<<i);
        }
        
        
    }
    
    
}

int main()
{
    uint32_t d = fu(0b01110110);

    printf("Result = %u\n", d);

    return 0;
}
